li.al:
the terms ``Agreed service" and ``Specified route"
                  mean: International air service pursuant to this Agreement and
                  the route specified in the Annex to this Agreement respectively;

the term ``Designated airline" means: an airline which
                  has been designated and authorized in accordance with Article
                  3 of this Agreement (Designation and Authorization);

the term ``Stores" means: articles, of a readily
                  consumable nature, for use or sale on board an aircraft during
                  flight including commissary supplies;

the airline holds a current Air Operator's
                    Certificate issued by the Aeronautical authorities of the
                    other Contracting Party;

the Government designating the airline is maintaining and
                    administering the standards set forth in Article 16 (Safety)
                    and Article 17 (Aviation Security);

in the Territory of the other Contracting Party to engage
                    directly and, at its discretion, through its agents in the
                    sale of air transportation and ancillary or supplemental services;

the interest of consumers of air transport products shall
                    be protected from any misuse of such information including
                    misleading presentation thereof;
